"title": "7308: Atonement, Day of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7308",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The most holy day of Israel's year (the tenth day of the seventh month) on which the high priest entered the Most Holy Place to offer sacrifices for the sins of the nation. Hebrews sees this day as symbolic of the achievements of Jesus Christ on the cross.</p>\n<h2>The priestly rituals on the Day of Atonement</h2>\n<h3>The priest's own preparations</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:4\">LEV 16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:6\">LEV 16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:11-Lev16:14\">LEV 16:11–16:14</a></p>\n<h3>The preparation of two male goats</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:7-Lev16:10\">LEV 16:7–16:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:10\">EXO 30:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:15-Lev16:19\">LEV 16:15–16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:10\">LEV 16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:20-Lev16:22\">LEV 16:20–16:22</a></p>\n<h3>Concluding procedures</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:23-Lev16:28\">LEV 16:23–16:28</a></p>\n<h3>Additional offerings on the Day of Atonement</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:8-Num29:11\">NUM 29:8–29:11</a></p>\n<h2>Features unique to the Day of Atonement</h2>\n<h3>The priest entered the Most Holy Place</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:7\">HEB 9:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:2\">LEV 16:2</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrifice was made for all the sins of all the people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:30\">LEV 16:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:10\">EXO 30:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:16-Lev16:17\">LEV 16:16–16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:21-Lev16:22\">LEV 16:21–16:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:34\">LEV 16:34</a></p>\n<h3>It was a festival requiring humility and fasting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:7\">NUM 29:7</a></strong> <em>This provides a contrast to all other religious festivals which were times of joyous celebration and feasting. “deny yourselves” includes the idea of fasting.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:29\">LEV 16:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:31\">LEV 16:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:27-Lev23:32\">LEV 23:27–23:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:9\">ACT 27:9</a></p>\n<h2>The Day of Atonement is paralleled and contrasted with the achievements of Jesus Christ in his death</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ entered the Most Holy Place</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:19-Heb6:20\">HEB 6:19–6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11-Heb9:12\">HEB 9:11–9:12</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's blood was offered in sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25\">ROM 3:25</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's sacrifice was outside the city gates</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:11-Heb13:12\">HEB 13:11–13:12</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's sacrifice was once for all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:25-Heb9:26\">HEB 9:25–9:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:12\">HEB 10:12</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's sacrifice gives inner rather than ritual cleansing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:13-Heb9:14\">HEB 9:13–9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:9-Heb9:10\">HEB 9:9–9:10</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's sacrifice gives access to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:20\">HEB 10:19–10:20</a></strong> <em>On the Day of Atonement no-one else was allowed to be in the Tent of Meeting, let alone in the Most Holy Place. Access into the intimate presence of God is now the right of all believers.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:17\">LEV 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51\">MAT 27:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:12\">EPH 3:12</a></p>",
